Hooded Man: This is different from what I heard! Why is
there a state of conflict between the Adventurer's Guild?

Fake Adventurer Psema: They're getting in the way! Don't
tell me you're just now realizing why I decided to
cooperate?

Fake Adventurer Psema: You were just being used! Well, it's
fine, isn't it? Your wish has been granted, after all.
Fake Adventurer Psema: You're so cute, so precious to you--

Clea: Psema...! I won't let you escape today, no matter
what.

Fake Adventurer Psema: Those Adventurer's Guild people are
so persistent. Just because they destroyed this trading hub,
they think they're all that, huh?

Fake Adventurer Psema: You know the ingredients for the
Dragon's Tear, right? Whether it's Kanonas or Fotizona, it
can be mass-produced anywhere!

Fake Adventurer Psema: I will spread my malice and pleasure
throughout the empire!
Clea: I said I won't let you escape.

Fake Adventurer Psema: Say hello to Celis-chan for me! Make
sure you buy us some time.
Clea: If you get in the way, I won't show any mercy.

Clea: Please give up. You won't be able to escape with those
wounds.

Hooded Man: We talked about it before, didn't we? Those who
are stopped by words are not adventurers...
Swift Celis: Clea... Are you okay?

Simos of the Unknown Night: Hey, Clea, are you enjoying the
good parts?
Simos of the Unknown Night: Now then, who is the traitor?

Simos of the Unknown Night: Didn't you hear from Agonia? The
black request letter is proof that a traitor has appeared.

Simos of the Unknown Night: I suppose the low-ranking
investigator was trying to make some extra money. Now then,
shall I see what's under that hood...

Melos the Hole Digger: Ugh... I've been given such an
unpleasant role...
Clea: Why... me... Why are you with Psema...?

Melos the Hole Digger: The reason I'm teaming up with such a
scumbag... is because Ect asked me to bring the healing
potion... and ordered me to betray you...

Melos the Hole Digger: That's why I sold out the
Adventurer's Guild... I'm the one who leaked the information
about transporting the giant crystal.

Melos the Hole Digger: Agonia-san found out... but it's for
the best... I did something bad to you... ugh!

Clea: Please don't talk anymore! Ect-chan has recovered and
wants to have a meal together!

Melos the Hole Digger: There's something that only I, a
traitor, can ask of you... It may be presumptuous of me...
but will you listen?

Melos the Hole Digger: I'm counting on you, Ect. Sorry for
always getting stuck with these unpleasant roles...

Simos of the Unknown Night: Do you have any last words to
leave us after breaking the three principles of the guild?

Melos the Hole Digger: It was fun being with all of you...
hehehe... exploring ruins, defeating bandits, catching
thieves...

Melos the Hole Digger: Please apologize to everyone...
especially... Agonia-san, Storge, and the Great Widow...
Melos the Hole Digger: ...I'm sorry... Ect... I'm sorry...

Simos of the Unknown Night: Ect... apologize in my place,
will you?

Simos of the Unknown Night: Damn it... leaving behind
troublesome things for someone like me... damn it...

parameters:
Loparo Raiders Executive: 'Regarding the recent carriage
attack... doesn't something seem fishy?'

Loparo Raiders Executive: I haven't heard any information
about merchants from Valt.

Loparo Raiders Executive: You're right, it's as you say, but
we don't have any options at the moment.

Loparo Raiders Executive: 'Due to the noble Pido's anti-
thief measures, we are in a state where we are struggling to
survive.'

Loparo Raiders Executive: If the carriage isn't carrying
merchants... just to be safe, I want you to head to the site
as well.

Loparo Raiders Executive: I believe it was a grassland
infested with bandits.

Mage Relm (It seems that the carriage attack was indeed
true, I need to hurry back and inform Nora and the others!)
